NAME
    evaldir - Evaluate directories into full paths
DESCRIPTION
    The EVALDIR command is for debugging purposes only, and is designed to test the evalDir() function. It converts a relative path (such as ~) into a full one.
SYNTAX
    evaldir [list of paths]
        Turn a relative path into a full path.
EXAMPLES
    evaldir /
        Shows the path to the root directory.
    evaldir ~
        Shows the path to the home directory.
    evaldir .
        Shows the path to the current directory.
